== Issues ==
During the installation of the glass and steel 'blade' architectural feature on the roof, a strange noise problem emerged. People reported that the building "whistles" (more like an intermittent hum) in windy weather. The sound is close to standard musical C (approximately 262 Hertz); some say it is like a "[[UFO]] landing" in sci-fi films. <ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.newscientisttech.com/channel/tech/mg19125631.300.html | title=Buildings that whistle in the wind | publisher=[[New Scientist]] Tech | date= [[4 August]] [[2006]]}}</ref> The noise also affected the production of local soap opera, [[Coronation Street]] with producers having to create extra background noise as the tower is close to the show's set. Despite apparently rectifying the problem, the humming sound can still be heard on occasion in the area, depending on wind direction.{{Fact|date=February 2008}}

Additionally, many residents of districts close to the city centre, including the [[Hulme]] area of Manchester, report a significant loss of television reception following construction of the tower.<ref> [http://gavinwhite.blogspot.com/2006/10/can-big-be-beautiful.html Can big be beautiful?]</ref> Effects have been reported as far away as [[Whalley Range]].{{Fact|date=February 2008}}

